{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Karate Club Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) Example\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates a compact **encoder → GCN → decoder** pipeline on the Karate Club graph.\n",
    "\n",
    "Each node has categorical and scalar features, which are embedded, processed through GCN layers, and finally used for link prediction via a dot-product decoder."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Node Features and Linear Projection\n",
    "\n",
    "- Club (categorical): embedded as a 4-dimensional vector via an embedding table of size `2×4` (8 trainable parameters).\n",
    "- Scalars: degree (normalized), betweenness, closeness → 3 dimensions per node.\n",
    "- Concatenation → `x0 ∈ ℝ⁷` per node.\n",
    "- Linear projection 7 → 10 dimensions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.nn.functional as F\n",
    "from torch_geometric.nn import GCNConv\n",
    "\n",
    "class KarateGCN(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, num_clubs=2, club_emb_dim=4, scalar_dim=3, hidden_dim=10):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.club_emb = nn.Embedding(num_clubs, club_emb_dim)\n",
    "        self.lin = nn.Linear(club_emb_dim + scalar_dim, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        self.conv1 = GCNConv(hidden_dim, hidden_dim, add_self_loops=True)\n",
    "        self.conv2 = GCNConv(hidden_dim, hidden_dim, add_self_loops=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def forward(self, club_idx, scalars, edge_index):\n",
    "        x = torch.cat([self.club_emb(club_idx), scalars], dim=1)\n",
    "        x = F.relu(self.lin(x))\n",
    "        x1 = self.conv1(x, edge_index)\n",
    "        y = F.relu(x1)\n",
    "        x2 = self.conv2(y, edge_index)\n",
    "        z = torch.cat([x1, x2], dim=1)\n",
    "        return x, x1, x2, z"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Decoder (Link Prediction)\n",
    "\n",
    "Dot-product between node embeddings: `σ(z_i^T z_j)` → probability of edge `(i, j)`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example: link prediction probability between node i and j\n",
    "def link_probability(z, i, j):\n",
    "    return torch.sigmoid(torch.dot(z[i], z[j]))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Shapes & Parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "- Linear output: `[N, 10]`\n",
    "- GCNConv1 output: `[N, 10]`\n",
    "- GCNConv2 output: `[N, 10]`\n",
    "- Final concatenated embedding `z`: `[N, 20]`\n",
    "- Total trainable parameters: 308"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Verify shapes and parameter count\n",
    "model = KarateGCN()\n",
    "total_params = sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters())\n",
    "print(\"Total trainable parameters:\", total_params)\n",
    "# Shapes can be checked after passing sample data through forward pass"
   ]
  }
